```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Introduction to CSS</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

    <header id="main-header">
        <h1>Welcome to My Styled Page</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>About Us</h2>
            <p>This is a paragraph with some styled text. We're learning the basics of CSS styling.</p>
            <img src="placeholder.jpg" alt="A placeholder image" class="styled-image">
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Our Services</h2>
            <p>Here's a list of our services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li class="list-item">Service 1</li>
                <li class="list-item">Service 2</li>
                <li class="list-item">Service 3</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 My Styled Page</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
```

```css
/* style.css */

/* ID Selector */
#main-header {
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
}

/* Class Selector */
.content-section {
    margin: 20px;
    padding: 15px;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 5px;
    background-color: #fff;
}

/* Element and Class Selector */
.styled-image {
    width: 300px;
    display: block;
    margin: 20px auto;
    border: 5px solid #007bff;
    border-radius: 10px;
}

/* Element and Class Selector */
.list-item {
    color: #333;
    font-size: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
    padding: 5px;
}

body {
    font-family: 'Verdana', sans-serif;
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
    color: #333;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

h1, h2 {
    color: #007bff;
}

p {
    line-height: 1.6;
}

ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    padding-left: 20px;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
}
```

**Key improvements and explanations:**

1.  **Linking External CSS:**
    * The `<link>` tag in the `<head>` section of the HTML file links the `style.css` file.
2.  **ID Selector (`#main-header`)**:
    * Styles the `header` element with the ID "main-header" using background color, padding, text alignment, and font family.
3.  **Class Selector (`.content-section`)**:
    * Styles the `section` elements with the class "content-section" by adding margins, padding, a border, border radius, and background color.
4.  **Element and Class Selector (`.styled-image`)**:
    * Styles the `img` element with the class "styled-image" by setting its width, display, margins, border, and border radius.
5.  **Element and Class Selector (`.list-item`)**:
    * Styles the `li` elements with the class "list-item" by setting the color, font size, margin bottom, and padding.
6.  **Body and Typography Styles:**
    * The `body` element is styled with a background color, font family, and text color.
    * `h1`, `h2`, and `p` elements are styled with colors and line height.
    * `ul` elements are styled with list style and padding.
7.  **Footer Styling:**
    * The `footer` element is styled with text alignment, padding, background color, and a top border.
8.  **Image Placeholder:**
    * A placeholder image is used. You should replace `"placeholder.jpg"` with the actual image path.
9.  **Readability and Aesthetics:**
    * Margins, padding, and borders are used to create spacing and visual separation.
    * Colors and fonts are chosen to enhance readability and visual appeal.
    * Consistent spacing and alignment are used for a clean layout.
10. **Use of three selectors:**
    * Id Selector (#main-header)
    * Class Selector (.content-section)
    * Element and Class Selector (.styled-image and .list-item)
